This paper is about categorizing search query entities in the recruitment domain, which is a task related to information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as distributional semantics and WordNet, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also employs machine learning algorithms, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
